## 1.8

设 $U = [u_1, u_2, u3]$

则:

$$
U^T M U =
\begin{bmatrix}
\frac{1}{2} \left(65-7 \sqrt{65}\right) c_1^2 m & 0 & 0 \\
0 & \frac{1}{2} \left(65 + 7\sqrt{65}\right) c_2^2 m & 0 \\
0 & 0 & 2 c_3^2 L^2 m \\
\end{bmatrix}
$$

$$
U^T K U =
\begin{bmatrix}
\left(65 - 8\sqrt{65}\right) c_1^2 k & 0 & 0 \\
0 & \left(65 + \sqrt{65}\right) c_2^2 k & 0 \\
0 & 0 & 2 c_3^2 g L m \\
\end{bmatrix}
$$

所以满足正交性

要求

$$U^T M U = I$$

解得

$$
\begin{cases}
c_1 = \frac{\sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{65 m-7 \sqrt{65} m}} = \sqrt {\frac{65 + 7 \sqrt{17}}{520 m}}\\
c_2 = \frac{\sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{7 \sqrt{65} m+65 m}} = \sqrt {\frac{65-7 \sqrt{65}}{520 m}} \\
c_3 = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2} L \sqrt{m}}
\end{cases}
$$

此时

$$
U^T K U = \Lambda =
\begin{bmatrix}
\frac{9 - \sqrt{65} }{8} \frac{k}{m} & 0 & 0 \\
0 & \frac{9 + \sqrt{65}}{8} \frac{k}{m} & 0 \\
0 & 0 & \frac{g}{L}
\end{bmatrix}
$$

## 1.10

原方程为

$$
M \ddot y + K y = F
$$

其中

$$
M = \begin{bmatrix}
m & 0 & 0 \\
0 & 4m & 0 \\
0 & 0 & 2m L^2
\end{bmatrix}
$$

$$
K = \begin{bmatrix}
2 k & -k & 0 \\
-k & k & 0 \\
0 & 0 & 2m g L
\end{bmatrix}
$$

$$
F = \begin{bmatrix}
\frac{F_0}{10}(r(t) - r(t-10) )\\
1.4\frac{F_0}{10}(r(t) - r(t-10) )\\
0
\end{bmatrix} = \frac{F_0}{10}(r(t) - r(t-10) )
\begin{bmatrix}
1\\
1.4\\
0
\end{bmatrix}
$$

令$y = U \eta$, 同时方程两端乘以$U^T$

则:

$$\ddot \eta + \Lambda \eta = U^T F$$


方程解耦为:

$$
\begin{cases}
\ddot{\eta}_1 + \lambda_1 \eta_1 &= \underbrace {\frac{\sqrt{298+\frac{406}{\sqrt{65}}}}{20 \sqrt{m}}}_{C_1} \frac{F_0}{10}(r(t) - r(t-10) ) \\
\ddot{\eta}_2 + \lambda_2 \eta_2 &= \underbrace {-\frac{\sqrt{298-\frac{406}{\sqrt{65}}}}{20 \sqrt{m}}}_{C_2} \frac{F_0}{10}(r(t) - r(t-10) )\\
\ddot{\eta}_3 + \lambda_3 \eta_3 &= 0
\end{cases}
$$

方程的特解为

\eta_2 &= \frac{C_2}{\lambda_2}\frac{F_0}{10}g_2(t) = -\frac{296 \sqrt{\frac{2}{3187 \sqrt{65}+25805}} \sqrt{m}}{5 k}\frac{F_0}{10}g_2(t)\\

所以

$$

\begin{pmatrix}
\frac{2 \left(195 + 17 \sqrt{65}\right)}{325 k}\frac{F_0}{10}g_1(t)+\frac{2 \left(195 - 17 \sqrt{65}\right) }{325 k}\frac{F_0}{10}g_2(t)\\
\frac{1235 + 157 \sqrt{65} }{650 k}\frac{F_0}{10}g_1(t)+\frac{1235-157 \sqrt{65} }{650 k}\frac{F_0}{10}g_2(t)\\

\end{pmatrix} \\
\approx \begin{pmatrix}

0.384735\frac{F_0}{k}g_1(t)-0.00473453\frac{F_0}{k}g_2(t)\\
0
\end{pmatrix}
$$

## 1.9

原方程为

$$
M \ddot y + K y = F
$$

其中

$$
M = \begin{bmatrix}
m & 0 & 0 \\
0 & 4m & 0 \\
0 & 0 & 2m L^2
\end{bmatrix}
$$

$$
K = \begin{bmatrix}
2 k & -k & 0 \\
-k & k & 0 \\
0 & 0 & 2m g L
\end{bmatrix}
$$

$$
F = \begin{bmatrix}
0\\
F_0 \cos \sqrt 2 t \sin \theta\\
F_0 L \cos \sqrt 2 t
\end{bmatrix}
$$

令$y = U \eta$, 同时方程两端乘以$U^T$

则:

$$\ddot \eta + \Lambda \eta = U^T F$$

方程解耦为:

$$
\begin{cases}
\ddot{\eta}_1 + \lambda_1 \eta_1 &= \frac{\sqrt{\frac{1}{2}+\frac{7}{2 \sqrt{65}}} F_0 \sin (\theta ) \cos \left(\sqrt{2} t\right)}{2 \sqrt{m}} \\
\ddot{\eta}_2 + \lambda_2 \eta_2 &= \frac{\sqrt{\frac{1}{2}-\frac{7}{2 \sqrt{65}}} F_0 \sin (\theta ) \cos \left(\sqrt{2} t\right)}{2 \sqrt{m}}\\
\ddot{\eta}_3 + \lambda_3 \eta_3 &= \frac{F_0 \cos \left(\sqrt{2} t\right)}{\sqrt{2} \sqrt{m}}
\end{cases}
$$

观察可知, 通过第三个方程可求出$\theta$, 然后代入到方程$F$右端
